  "text": "The TLS configuration flows from Prometheus configuration through prometheus-common to the actual tls.Config used in HTTP clients. The chain begins with ScrapeConfig and RemoteWriteConfig (prometheus/config/config.go:747 and prometheus/config/config.go:1419 respectively), both of which embed HTTPClientConfig from prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:332. HTTPClientConfig contains a TLSConfig field (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:346), which defines all TLS options including CA certificates, client certificates, keys, and TLS version constraints. The TLSConfig struct is defined at prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:1199 and includes validation via the Validate() method (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:1253). For scrape target connections, prometheus/scrape/scrape.go:2260 defines newScrapeClient() which calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig() (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:605). This function creates an HTTP client with a properly configured RoundTripper by calling NewRoundTripperFromConfigWithContext (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:629), which in turn calls NewTLSConfigWithContext (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:1138) to convert the TLSConfig structure into a standard Go tls.Config. For mutable certificate files (CA, client cert, or key files), NewTLSRoundTripperWithContext (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:1382) creates a tlsRoundTripper that automatically reloads certificates by comparing file hashes on each request. The tlsRoundTripper type (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:1350) wraps a base RoundTripper and monitors TLSRoundTripperSettings for certificate changes. The updateRootCA function (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:1339) parses PEM-encoded CA certificates and updates the tls.Config.RootCAs certificate pool. For remote write operations, NewWriteClient (prometheus/storage/remote/client.go:183) similarly uses config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with ClientConfig that embeds HTTPClientConfig, establishing the same TLS flow. Remote read operations use NewReadClient (prometheus/storage/remote/client.go:151) with the same pattern. The discovery modules, such as TritonSD (prometheus/discovery/triton/triton.go:68), directly instantiate TLSConfig and call NewTLSConfig() (prometheus/discovery/triton/triton.go:154) to create tls.Config objects. Throughout the flow, TLSVersion (prometheus-common/config/http_config.go:70) is used to specify minimum and maximum TLS versions with proper marshaling/unmarshaling support for YAML and JSON formats. This architecture ensures that TLS certificates can be updated dynamically without restarting Prometheus, while maintaining strict validation of configuration parameters across both scrape targets and remote write/read operations."
}

